    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Matthew 25:30. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Matthew 25:30",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And cast ye the unprofitable servant — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Who has so wickedly abused my goodness; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "into outer darkness ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— The darkness which is without the heavenly city, even the horrible darkness of hell. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "There, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "instead of the light and joy possessed by those who are admitted to the marriage- supper of the Lamb, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "shall be weeping and gnashing of teeth — Through the worm that dieth not, and the fire that is not quenched. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "There shall be the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "weeping ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "of the careless, thoughtless sinner, and the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "gnashing of teeth ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "of the proud and stubborn. See notes on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 8:12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 13:42",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 22:13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". But why does this servant meet with this punishment? What had he done? It is true he had not done good. But neither is he charged with doing any harm. Why, for this reason, for ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "barely doing no harm, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "he is consigned to outer darkness. He is pronounced a wicked, because he was a ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "slothful, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "an ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "unprofitable servant. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "So ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "mere harmlessness, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "on which many build their hope of salvation, was the cause of his damnation! Observe this well, reader; slothful servants, who do nothing with respect to the purpose of their being sent into the world, nothing to answer the end of their birth and baptism, who are no way serviceable to the glory of God, or the good of others, will be reckoned with as unprofitable servants. A slothful servant is a withered member in the body, a barren tree in the vineyard, an idle drone in the hive, that is good for nothing. In one sense, indeed, we are all unprofitable servants, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Luke 17:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". We cannot profit God, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Job 22:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; but to others, and to ourselves, it is required that we be profitable; and if we be not, Christ will not own us as his servants.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
